---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import SectionHeading from '../components/SectionHeading.astro';
import CTABanner from '../components/CTABanner.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Partnership — 1404 | Full Technology Department"
  description="A permanent technology department for your company. CTO leadership, custom engineering, AI agent operations, and continuous R&D. Managed by 1404."
>
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 pt-40 pb-24 md:pb-32">

    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="mb-20">
      <h1 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl text-text-primary leading-tight">
        Partnership
      </h1>
      <p class="text-text-secondary text-lg mt-6 leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
        The full technology department, managed by 1404.
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- What a Partnership Is -->
    <div class="mb-24">
      <div class="space-y-6 text-text-body text-base leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          A partnership is a permanent technology department for your company. That means a CTO setting strategy, engineers building custom systems around how your operations actually work, every agent suite deployed and managed, and a research function tracking what's coming next in your industry.
        </p>
        <p>
          The point is that you stop thinking about technology entirely. You have a department whose entire job is handling it — vendors, IT projects, AI, systems, everything. Individual agent suites solve specific problems. A partnership turns technology into a structural advantage that gets stronger every month.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Four Pillars -->
    <div class="mb-24">
      <SectionHeading title="What's included" />

      <div class="space-y-16">

        <!-- CTO Leadership -->
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl text-text-primary mb-6">CTO Leadership</h3>
          <p class="text-text-body text-base leading-relaxed">
            We set strategy, define architecture, and build a technology roadmap — and then we execute it. Weekly calls with your team, vendor evaluation with real technical depth, and one person accountable for every technology decision in your company. Most companies make these decisions by committee or by whoever had the most convincing sales rep — that's how you end up with twelve disconnected tools and no strategy.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Custom Engineering -->
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl text-text-primary mb-6">Custom Engineering</h3>
          <p class="text-text-body text-base leading-relaxed">
            Unified systems built around how your company actually operates. Every module talks to every other module natively — project management talks to labor forecasting, purchase orders talk to inventory, and scheduling feeds directly into financials. When a project manager updates a schedule, the labor forecast recalculates automatically. One system, complete information, built as one thing from the start instead of duct-taped together after the fact.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Agent Operations -->
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl text-text-primary mb-6">Agent Operations</h3>
          <p class="text-text-body text-base leading-relaxed">
            Every agent suite deployed simultaneously — financial intelligence, executive operations, business development, acquisitions, exit preparation. The suites share context with each other, so the financial agents know what business development is tracking and the executive agents know what the acquisition pipeline looks like. Partnership clients get every suite we build, including new ones as we develop them.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Research & Development -->
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl text-text-primary mb-6">Research &amp; Development</h3>
          <p class="text-text-body text-base leading-relaxed">
            A dedicated research function that continuously tracks developments in AI, industry technology, and emerging tools. Capabilities that work for one client get rolled out to everyone. If a new model ships that changes what's possible, we've usually already been testing it. That's what keeps your company current — a team watching for what matters so you don't have to.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- How It Works -->
    <div class="mb-24">
      <SectionHeading title="How it works" />

      <div class="space-y-10">
        <div class="border-l-2 border-copper-dim pl-8">
          <p class="font-mono text-sm text-copper mb-2">Discovery</p>
          <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm">1&ndash;2 weeks</p>
          <p class="text-text-body text-base leading-relaxed mt-3">
            We learn your operations end to end. Every workflow, every pain point, every system you're currently using and every spreadsheet filling the gaps between them. We map where you are, where you need to be, and what the fastest path between those two points looks like. No templates, no assumptions.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-2 border-copper-dim pl-8">
          <p class="font-mono text-sm text-copper mb-2">Foundation</p>
          <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm">4&ndash;8 weeks</p>
          <p class="text-text-body text-base leading-relaxed mt-3">
            The core system goes live. The modules your operations need most get built first, and your team starts using them immediately. Agent suites get deployed alongside the platform, so from week one your company has both the systems and the intelligence layer running on top of them. We iterate weekly based on what your team runs into, so nothing sits broken for long.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-2 border-copper-dim pl-8">
          <p class="font-mono text-sm text-copper mb-2">Operations</p>
          <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm">Ongoing</p>
          <p class="text-text-body text-base leading-relaxed mt-3">
            Continuous development. New modules ship as needs emerge, and new agent capabilities roll out as we build them. CTO calls every week, system improvements every sprint, and a research function running in the background that surfaces opportunities and threats before they become obvious. The system grows with your business because the department behind it never stops working.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-2 border-copper pl-8">
          <p class="font-mono text-sm text-copper mb-2">Maturity</p>
          <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm">Year 2+</p>
          <p class="text-text-body text-base leading-relaxed mt-3">
            By year two, things start to look meaningfully different. The system knows your operations deeply. Agents anticipate problems before they surface. Institutional knowledge is embedded in the technology itself — not in someone's head, not in a shared drive nobody checks. The gap between you and companies that started later keeps widening.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- The Compounding Advantage -->
    <div class="mb-24">
      <SectionHeading title="What the system becomes over time" />

      <div class="space-y-6 text-text-body text-base leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          The real argument for a partnership over individual suites is what the system becomes over time. The agents learn more about your operations over time — month over month, the institutional knowledge deepens. After a year, the system understands patterns and relationships in your business that no single person could track on their own.
        </p>
        <p>
          After two years, the gap between you and a comparable company is hard to close. After five, it's essentially permanent. What you build in year one makes year two more effective, which makes year three more effective. Companies that start early tend to set the pace in their market rather than trying to match it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Closing -->
    <div class="border-t border-border pt-16">
      <p class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl text-text-primary leading-snug max-w-3xl">
        The longer the system runs, the more it knows about your business, and the harder that becomes for a competitor to replicate.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTABanner />
</PageLayout>
